# Renderer Module

## Module Purpose and Responsibilities

The Renderer module is a 2D batch-rendering pipeline built on top of DirectX 11. It is responsible for:

- Owning and managing all GPU resource abstractions: vertex buffers, index buffers, shaders, and textures.
- Collecting per-frame draw requests (quads, sprites, strings, UI quads, UI strings) that are emitted by other systems as ECS events.
- Sorting and batching those requests by texture and by draw layer, then submitting each batch to the GPU in a single indexed draw call.
- MSDF font atlas generation at load time and MSDF glyph rendering at draw time.
- Providing a thin `Renderer` / `RenderCommand` facade over the platform API so that higher-level code never touches DirectX directly.

The module sits entirely inside `PigeonLib` and has two sub-trees:

| Sub-tree | Location |
|---|---|
| Abstract / engine layer | `Code/PigeonLib/Pigeon/Renderer/` |
| DirectX 11 backend | `Code/PigeonLib/Platform/DirectX11/` |

---

## Layered Architecture

```
Renderer2DSystem  (ECS System – entry point each frame)
    └── file-scope free functions (anonymous namespace in Renderer2DSystem.cpp)
            ├── Renderer / RenderCommand  (thin static facade)
            │       └── RendererAPI  (abstract interface)
            │               └── Dx11RendererAPI  (DirectX 11 concrete)
            ├── VertexBuffer / IndexBuffer / Shader / Texture2D
            │       └── Dx11VertexBuffer / Dx11IndexBuffer / Dx11Shader / Dx11Texture2D
            └── Dx11Context  (device + swap-chain owner)
```

Factory methods (`VertexBuffer::Create`, `Shader::Create`, etc.) switch on `RendererAPI::GetAPI()` to return either a `Dx11*` or a `Testing*` implementation. In production builds the default is `DirectX11`; in `Testing` builds it is `Testing`.

---

## ECS Integration

`Renderer2DSystem` is a `pg::System`. Each frame its `Update` method:

1. Reads singletons: `OrthographicCameraComponent`, `ResourceMapSingletonComponent`, `EngineConfigSingletonComponent`.
2. If `RendererDataSingletonComponent` does not yet exist, creates it (calling `Init`) and emplaces it deferred.
3. Calls the file-scope `Render` function.

### SystemAccessDecl

| Set | Types |
|---|---|
| `addSet` | `RendererDataSingletonComponent` |
| `writeSet` | `RendererDataSingletonComponent` |
| `readSet` | `EngineConfigSingletonComponent`, `OrthographicCameraComponent`, `ResourceMapSingletonComponent`, `DrawQuadInFrameEvent`, `DrawSpriteInFrameEvent`, `DrawStringInFrameEvent`, `DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent`, `DrawUIStringInFrameEvent` |

---

## Scene Lifecycle (per frame)

```
Update()
  │
  ├─ [first frame] Init()
  │       allocates GPU VertexBuffer (BATCH_MAX_COUNT * VERTEX_STRIDE bytes, DYNAMIC)
  │       allocates GPU IndexBuffer  (BATCH_MAX_COUNT * INDEX_STRIDE / 4 entries, DYNAMIC)
  │       looks up QuadShader and TextShader from ResourceMapSingletonComponent
  │
  └─ Render()
          │
          ├─ Clear()          SetClearColor(0.3, 0.3, 0.3, 1) → ClearRenderTargetView
          │
          ├─ BeginScene()
          │       RenderCommand::Begin()  — handles pending resize, sets render target, sets viewport
          │       Bind VertexBuffer, IndexBuffer, default texture, QuadShader
          │       UploadUniformMat4("u_ViewProjection", camera VP matrix)
          │
          ├─ ProcessRenderRequests()   — iterate all in-frame events, fill CPU batch buffers
          │
          └─ EndScene()
                  Flush()             — GPU upload + draw call per batch
                  RenderCommand::End()
                  Unbind VertexBuffer, IndexBuffer
```

`RenderCommand::End` (`Dx11RendererAPI::End`) asserts initialization but performs no GPU work; the swap-chain `Present` is driven by the window/application layer, not the renderer.

