## In-Frame Event Types

These are pure data structs placed as ECS components on temporary entities for one frame. `Renderer2DSystem` reads them and then they are gone.

| Struct | Key fields | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `DrawQuadInFrameEvent` | `glm::mat4 m_Transform`, `glm::vec3 m_Color`, `glm::vec3 m_Origin`, `pg::UUID m_TextureID` | If `m_TextureID.IsNull()` uses solid color + default texture; otherwise samples provided texture. |
| `DrawUIQuadInFrameEvent` | Same fields as above | Structurally identical to `DrawQuadInFrameEvent`; treated identically in the system. |
| `DrawSpriteInFrameEvent` | `pg::Sprite m_Sprite` | Wraps a `Sprite` value which carries transform, tex-coords rect, texture UUID, and origin. |
| `DrawStringInFrameEvent` | `pg::S_Ptr<pg::Font> m_Font`, `std::string m_String`, `glm::mat4 m_Transform`, `glm::vec4 m_Color`, `float m_Kerning`, `float m_Linespacing` | Uses a direct font pointer. |
| `DrawUIStringInFrameEvent` | `pg::UUID m_FontID`, `std::string m_String`, `glm::mat4 m_Transform`, `glm::vec4 m_Color`, `float m_Kerning`, `float m_Linespacing` | Looks up font from `ResourceMapSingletonComponent::m_FontMap` by UUID. |

