## Abstract GPU Resource Types

All abstract types live in `Pigeon/Renderer/`. Factory static methods dispatch to the concrete implementation based on `RendererAPI::GetAPI()`.

### `VertexBuffer` (`Buffer.h`)

```cpp
class VertexBuffer {
    virtual void Bind() const = 0;
    virtual void Unbind() const = 0;
    virtual void SetVertices(const float* vertices, unsigned int count, unsigned int countOffset) = 0;
    virtual void AppendVertices(const float* vertices, unsigned int count, unsigned int countOffset) = 0;
    static pg::S_Ptr<VertexBuffer> Create(const float* vertices, uint32_t size, uint32_t stride);
};
```

### `IndexBuffer` (`Buffer.h`)

```cpp
class IndexBuffer {
    virtual void Bind() const = 0;
    virtual void Unbind() const = 0;
    virtual uint32_t GetCount() const = 0;
    virtual void SetIndices(const uint32_t* indices, unsigned int count, unsigned int countOffset) = 0;
    virtual void AppendIndices(const uint32_t* indices, unsigned int count, unsigned int countOffset) = 0;
    static pg::S_Ptr<IndexBuffer> Create(const uint32_t* indices, uint32_t size);
};
```

### `Shader` (`Shader.h`)

```cpp
class Shader {
    virtual void Bind() const = 0;
    virtual void Unbind() const = 0;
    virtual const std::string& GetName() const = 0;
    virtual void UploadUniformInt(const std::string& name, int value) const = 0;
    virtual void UploadUniformFloat(const std::string& name, float value) const = 0;
    virtual void UploadUniformFloat2(const std::string& name, const glm::vec2& value) const = 0;
    virtual void UploadUniformFloat3(const std::string& name, const glm::vec3& value) const = 0;
    virtual void UploadUniformFloat4(const std::string& name, const glm::vec4& value) const = 0;
    virtual void UploadUniformMat3(const std::string& name, const glm::mat3& matrix) const = 0;
    virtual void UploadUniformMat4(const std::string& name, const glm::mat4& matrix) const = 0;
    static pg::S_Ptr<Shader> Create(const std::string& filepath);
    static pg::S_Ptr<Shader> Create(const std::string& name, const char* vertexSrc, const char* fragmentSrc, const char* buffLayout);
};
```

`Shader` also owns a `BufferLayout m_Layout` (populated during `Compile`) and exposes it via `protected GetLayout()`.

`ShaderLibrary` is a helper map (`std::unordered_map<string, S_Ptr<Shader>>`) with `Add`, `Load`, `Get`, `Exists`.

### `BufferLayout` / `BufferElement` (`Shader.h`)

`BufferLayout` is an ordered list of `BufferElement` values. Each element carries a `ShaderDataType`, a semantic name, a byte size, and a byte offset (computed by `CalculateOffsetsAndStride`). The DirectX 11 backend parses these to build `D3D11_INPUT_ELEMENT_DESC` arrays.

### `Texture` / `Texture2D` / `Texture2DArray` (`Texture.h`)

```cpp
class Texture {
    virtual void Bind(uint32_t slot = 0) const = 0;
    virtual uint32_t GetWidth() const;
    virtual uint32_t GetHeight() const;
};

class Texture2D : public Texture {
    virtual glm::vec4 GetTexCoordsRect(glm::vec2 pixelsOffset, glm::vec2 pixelsSize) const = 0;
    static pg::S_Ptr<Texture2D> Create(const std::string& path);
    static pg::S_Ptr<Texture2D> Create(unsigned int width, unsigned int height,
                                        unsigned int channels, const unsigned char* data);
    static bool FlipY();
};

class Texture2DArray : public Texture {
    static pg::S_Ptr<Texture2DArray> Create(unsigned int count);
    virtual void Append(const std::string& path) = 0;
    virtual unsigned int GetCount() const = 0;
    virtual unsigned int GetMaxCount() const = 0;
};
```

`Texture2DArray` is declared but its DirectX 11 implementation asserts `NOT IMPLEMENTED` on all methods.

`TextureData` is a value struct holding `m_TextureType`, dimensions, channels, a `S_Ptr<Texture2D>`, and a `pg::UUID m_TextureID`. It is what `Font`'s constructor fills in when creating the MSDF atlas.

`EMappedTextureType` distinguishes `eQuad` (normal colour/sprite texture) from `eText` (MSDF atlas), which drives shader selection in `Flush`.

