## `Sprite` (`Sprite.h`)

```cpp
class Sprite {
    Sprite(const glm::mat4 transform, const glm::vec4 texCoords,
           const pg::UUID& textureID, const glm::vec3 origin = glm::vec3(0.f, 1.f, 0.f));
    void SetTransform(const glm::mat4& transform);
    void SetTexCoords(const glm::vec4& texCoords);
    void SetOrigin(const glm::vec3& origin);
    const glm::mat4& GetTransform() const;
    const glm::vec4& GetTexCoordsRect() const;  // (uMin, vMin, uMax, vMax)
    const glm::vec3& GetOrigin() const;
    const pg::UUID& GetTextureID() const;
};
```

Note: the default `origin` for `Sprite` is `(0, 1, 0)` (top-left of the quad), whereas `DrawQuad`/`DrawLayerBatch` typically receives `(0, 0, 0)`.

